description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department of Gastroenterology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Consultant Gastroenterologist with a clinical and academic interest in inflammatory bowel disease (IBD). This is a substantive post based at the Lister Hospital in Stevenage 4 days per week with one day at the University of Hertfordshire and comprises 10 programmed activities (PAs) including an on-call commitment to the emergency endoscopy rota. The post does not include a commitment to the general medical on-call rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate will be expected to have a significant clinical and academic research interest in IBD and hold an MD or PhD in IBD related research and will be responsible for the development of treatment pathways for IBD patients as well as recruiting patients to IBD trials. The candidate will develop their IBD academic interest at the University of Hertfordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Demand for Gastroenterology outpatient and endoscopy services is consistently high so the East and North Hertfordshire NHS Trust is seeking to appoint a new, enthusiastic and dynamic Consultant Gastroenterologist to join our existing Gastroenterology colleagues as soon as possible. The successful applicant will work closely with the existing Gastroenterologists to provide a high standard Gastroenterology service to the Trust. This post is based at the Lister Hospital in Stevenage; however, clinics can be at any of three sites, Lister Hospital, the New QEII Hospital in Welwyn Garden City or Hertford County Hospital, Hertford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following the investment of £150 million in major new facilities at the Lister, along with a £30 million New QEII hospital built by the local clinical commissioning group, the East and North Hertfordshire NHS Trust has brought together all its specialist emergency and inpatient services at the Stevenage hospital. Our state-of–the-art clinical facilities include a major new Emergency Department, the Hertfordshire Cardiology Centre (which includes a 24/7 PPCI service), new scanning centre, MacMillan chemotherapy unit, ward as well as a superbly designed and kitted endoscopy unit within the day Surgery Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The National Bowel Cancer Screening Programme was implemented in 2008 and Bowelscope flexible sigmoidoscopy screening in 2015. There is endoscopic sub-specialisation with ERCP, video capsule endoscopy and upper GI cancer services including provision of a regional GI Laser service based at the Lister Hospital. Recent developments include a nutrition service and local viral hepatology service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a new 4 roomed state of the art endoscopy unit at the Lister Hospital site and a two roomed endoscopy unit within the New QEII Hospital at Welwyn Garden City. Both units are JAG accredited and are fully kitted with state of the art equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our existing Gastroenterologists work across sites, supported by a newly expanded Gastrointestinal surgical department, specialist nurses, GP and nurse endoscopists. The job plan for this post includes a 1 in 11 GI bleeding rota that incorporates a 24/7 bleed service and some routine endoscopy at weekends whilst on-call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be on the Specialist Register, or be within 6 months of doing so, at the time of interview. Applications from those wishing to work part-time or job share are welcomed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is imperative that you also attach your CV to your application as this is an integral part of the application process. Please ensure to supply the names and addresses of referees. This must cover a period of 3 years with no gaps, one of whom must be your current employer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Dr Simon Greenfield Job title: Clinical Director for Gastroenterology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:  simon.greenfield@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01438 284245&lt;/p&gt;
